```
...
Zod is a third-party library included with Qwik City that lets you define a validation schema for a JS object.
The Zod schema can be passed as the second argument to the `routeAction$` function:
```
import { routeAction$, zod$, z } from '@builder.io/qwik-city';
const useFormSubmit = routeAction$((data) => {
return { success: true }
},
zod$({
summary: z.string().min(2),
body: z.string().min(2),
})
);
```
Qwik City will validate the form data object against this schema.

